description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi announced the celebration of Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel's 150th birth anniversary starting October 31 and Birsa Munda's from November 15. He encouraged participation through social media, highlighting their shared vision of national unity. Modi also mentioned the significance of his visit to Birsa Munda's birthplace last year.
title: PM Modi's 'unity' call to mark 150th birth anniversary of Sardar Patel, Birsa Munda

description: Fresh violence erupted in Manipur's Imphal West and Bishnupur districts with suspected militants using firearms and bombs. Attacks occurred in Koutruk Ching Leikai village around 7pm and Tronglaobi village at 9pm. No fatalities were reported. Two members of the People's Liberation Army were arrested.
title: Militants open fire, hurl bombs as fresh violence hits Manipur

description: At a Trump rally in New York City, several MAGA speakers, including Sid Rosenberg and David Rem, made racist and inflammatory remarks about illegal immigrants and Vice President Kamala Harris. Comedian Tony Hinchcliffe also made a controversial comment about Puerto Rico, drawing criticism from Harris' campaign.
title: Insults, offensive jokes and racist comments: MAGA speakers attack Kamala Harris from MSG

description: Tamil actor Vijay, founder of Tamilaga Vettri Kazhagam, declared DMK as a political enemy and BJP as an ideological adversary at TVK's first political conference. Criticizing DMK's portrayal of BJP and its governance, he emphasized TVK's independent stance and openness to alliances ahead of the 2026 Tamil Nadu state elections.
title: DMK political enemy, BJP ideological foe: Actor Vijay

description: Assam CM Himanta Biswa Sarma, also in charge of BJP's assembly polls in Jharkhand, calls the state a challenging battleground. Despite five Assam constituencies facing bypolls, Sarma prioritizes Jharkhand's campaign, entrusting Assam's bypoll efforts to ministers and party members. He remains uncertain about participating directly in the Assam campaign.

description: RSS general secretary Dattatreya Hosabale clarified that BJP President J P Nadda's remarks on BJP being 'self-sufficient' were about fostering independence, not creating a rift. He emphasized the unity and familial bond between RSS and BJP, countering media reports of discord.
title: 'Differences natural in a family': RSS scotches talk of rift with BJP

description: Diwali in Bikaner, Rajasthan, features a unique celebration with the recital of an Urdu version of the Ramayan by Maulvi Badshah Shah Hussain Rana Lakhnavi, dating back to 1935. This 12-year-old tradition underscores communal harmony and is highlighted by vivid couplets depicting scenes of the epic, attracting widespread community participation and scholarly attention.
title: Recital of Urdu Ramayan heralds Bikaner’s Diwali

description: Kolkata filmmaker Sriyanka Ray has been posthumously honored with an independent Emmy for her short documentary 'Homeroom Dreams,' focusing on New York's housing issues for the impoverished. It's her first independent Emmy win as a director and producer, marking her 13th nomination.
title: Kolkata woman wins Emmy a year after death in Bolivia

description: Isro is set to launch its first electric propulsion-led spacecraft in December, significantly reducing satellite mass. Upcoming missions include Gaganyaan in 2026, Chandrayaan-4 in 2028, and Chandrayaan-5 post-2028. The Indo-US NISAR satellite is prepped for a February launch, advancing earth imaging technology.
title: India's first home-grown electric propulsion satellite to be launched in Dec: Isro chief

description: A Yale expert reveals SMA drug Risdiplam could cost Rs 3,000 annually with local production, vastly cheaper than Rs 72 lakh due to patents. A Kerala court case highlights treatment affordability issues and insufficient government financial assistance and crowdfunding efforts for patients.
title: Rs 72 lakh/year rare-disease drug can be made for Rs 3,000/year, HC told

description: PM Narendra Modi addresses the rise of cyber scams involving 'digital arrests,' emphasizing that no government agency demands money over the phone. He outlines steps for digital security: stop, think, and act. Victims should report scams to the national cyber helpline 1930 and cybercrime.gov.in. Modi highlights the need for public awareness to combat fraudsters.
title: PM Modi flags ‘digital arrests’, says no government body issues phone threats

description: India has significantly increased its defence exports, with Armenia being the top buyer of weapon systems like Akash missiles and Pinaka rockets. The export success includes deals with other nations such as the Philippines and Brazil, while domestic defence production also reaches new heights aiming for higher targets in the future.
title: US, France & Armenia top three buyers of Indian defence exports

description: Rat trap manufacturers have petitioned Bombay High Court against the Animal Welfare Board of India's ban on glue traps, arguing it infringes their legal rights. The ban, they claim, violates provisions that are essential for pest control in various industries, including hospitality and Indian Railways. Manufacturers argue glue traps provide a non-poisonous solution to rodent infestation.

description: In the Bandra West constituency, sitting MLA Ashish Shelar faces Congress's Asif Zakaria again, who lost to him in 2019. Residents are concerned about issues like congestion, noise, and illegal encroachments, while Zakaria criticizes wasteful expenditures and Shelar aims to rehabilitate slums and reduce traffic.

description: Shiv Sena released its second list of 20 candidates, now totaling 65 nominees, including ex-Congress members Milind Deora and Sanjay Nirupam. The list also includes several former BJP members and accommodates new candidates such as Rajendra Gavit in place of dropped sitting MLA Srinivas Wanaga.

description: Horoscope Today: Read daily horoscope predictions for October 28, 2024. Know all about the astrological events and influences that will be affecting each of the 12 zodiac signs. Get ready to discover what the stars have in store for you today.

description: Following a serious ragging incident at Tripura Medical College, an FIR has been registered against 18 students who have been fined ₹10 lakh collectively and suspended for a year from hostels. The students are accused of forcing juniors to shave their heads and pressuring female students to propose to seniors.

description: The Sri Lankan navy arrested 12 fishermen from Tamil Nadu and seized their trawler for allegedly poaching in Lankan waters near Point Pedro in Jaffna district. The fishermen were handed over for legal proceedings. To date in 2024, 62 Indian fishing boats and 462 fishermen have been detained by the Lankan navy.

description: Since mid-October, a surge of anonymous online hoax threats has disrupted over 350 flights, causing significant delays and financial losses for airlines like IndiGo, Vistara, and Akasa. Authorities are collaborating with social media platforms, international agencies, and the Intelligence Bureau to tackle the threats. The government plans to amend aviation laws for stringent penalties.

description: In 1899, a unique artillery shell bearing a plum cake and Christmas greetings marked a truce during the Boer War in Ladysmith, South Africa. This historical artifact, now housed at Jabalpur's AOC Museum, is celebrated by the Indian Army through an annual competition, honoring a 125-year-old colonial tradition.
title: Shell on Christmas cake that defined 1899 Boer war truce now adorns MP museum

description: At a Trump rally in New York City, comedian Tony Hinchcliffe criticized Vice President Kamala Harris for receiving endorsements from Hollywood celebrities and compared the Democratic Party to a P Diddy party. Hinchcliffe also attacked Hillary Clinton and made offensive remarks toward Puerto Ricans and Latino immigrants.

description: External Affairs minister S Jaishankar emphasized the need for Maharashtra to align with the Centre for enhanced international investments and addressed issues like the India-China border standoff and counter-terrorism efforts. He highlighted the significance of federal competition and the India-Middle East Economic Corridor.

description: CJI D Y Chandrachud emphasizes that India's cooperative federalism grants states autonomy and doesn't mandate adherence to central policies. He highlights the importance of dialogue, both cooperative and contentious, in promoting federalism, and notes the diverse and unique relationships each state has with the Centre.

description: Jordynne Grace lost her Knockouts World Championship title to Masha Slammovich at Bound For Glory 2024 after holding it for over 250 days. Her TNA contract expires in January 2025, leading to speculations of her potential move to WWE. However, no confirmed information supports this yet. description: Dhanteras, marking the start of Diwali, celebrates wealth, health, and prosperity with prayers to Lord Dhanvantari. The festival, on Kartik's thirteenth day, involves purchasing valuable items and exchanging heartfelt wishes. description: Two Pakistani terrorists suspected to be from Jaish-e-Mohammad carried out a deadly ambush on an Indian Army convoy in J&K's Gulmarg, killing two soldiers and two porters. After infiltrating the region eight weeks prior, the assailants targeted the convoy with grenades and automatic weapons before fleeing.

description: Terming the controversy over the PM's visit for Ganpati puja as unnecessary, CJI D Y Chandrachud stated that such visits are social and judicial matters are never discussed. He emphasized the mature boundary between the judiciary and political executive in upholding judicial independence.

description: Delhi's air quality worsened to 'very poor' due to rising AQI despite a decrease in stubble burning share. Research highlights a massive loss of groundwater in Punjab and Haryana, driven by urbanization and agricultural demands, triggering concerns about future agricultural productivity and soil quality.

The agreement marks a significant step in resolving the four-year-long military standoff.

description: Diwali, the Festival of Lights, is celebrated globally among Indian communities. Signifying the victory of light over darkness, it brings joy, love, and positivity. description: Western Railway has temporarily restricted platform ticket sales at selected Mumbai Division stations to manage overcrowding during the festive season until November 8, 2024. description: Despite government intervention, hoax threats to Indian commercial flights persist, affecting over 350 flights in the past 15 days and causing significant financial losses and delays. description: Diwali, the festival of lights, will be celebrated on October 31, 2024, with the Vishva Hindu Parishad confirming the date. The celebrations coincide with Amavasya, and auspicious timings for Lakshmi Puja are set. Deepotsav and Hanuman Jayanti will take place on October 30.

The incident occurred at 2:55 a.m. with two passengers in critical condition. Authorities are probing the circumstances as passengers reportedly attempted to board moving general class coaches.
title: 9 injured in stampede at Mumbai's Bandra railway station

description: In a remarkable week for New Zealand cricket, the Black Caps secured their first-ever Test series win in India, ending a 36-year winless streak, while the White Ferns claimed their maiden ICC Women's T20 World Cup title in Dubai. These unprecedented victories have thrust New Zealand cricket into unprecedented global prominence.
title: NZ Cricket's Historic Week: Test series win in India & Women's T20 WC triumph

description: Delhi's air quality worsened significantly, with AQI hitting 'very poor' and 'severe' levels at various locations. Residents report breathing difficulties, while government measures appear ineffective. Amid rising pollution, the Delhi government has banned firecrackers until January. Political tensions escalate over pollution management, with BJP and AAP trading accusations over the deteriorating situation and public health impact.
title: Delhi air: AQI plummets to 'very poor' category, many feel 'suffocated'

description: Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu is hopeful for Trump’s return to the presidency, expecting beneficial policies for Israel despite Trump's mixed messages. Analysts suggest a Trump victory would provide Netanyahu greater freedom, contrasting Biden's more critical stance. Meanwhile, Palestinians remain skeptical of both candidates.
title: Trump or Harris: Who is Israel PM Netanyahu likely to support?

description: In a real-life imitation of the movie 'Special 26', seven imposters posing as ED officers raided a businessman's house in Delhi, demanding Rs 5 crore over alleged cash withdrawals. They held him overnight, but fled when the victim's lawyer asked for ID verification at the bank, alerting authorities.
title: Fake ED team raids businessman’s house in Delhi, tries to extort Rs 5 crore

description: Donald Trump claims that Google CEO Sundar Pichai called him to praise his visit to McDonald's, labeling it a significant event. Trump has made similar claims about calls from Apple’s Tim Cook and META’s Mark Zuckerberg, though these figures haven't confirmed such interactions. Trump's supporters believe these claims indicate his potential election success.
title: Trump bowls a Google-y, says Pichai called to compliment his McD sortie

description: Former Pakistan batter Basit Ali believes that India's overconfidence led to their first home series loss in 12 years against New Zealand. He criticized India's batting and bowling performances while highlighting the absence of Mohammed Shami for the upcoming Border-Gavaskar Trophy, predicting difficulties for India's fast bowling attack in Australia.
title: Indian players were 'overconfident': Ex-Pak cricketer

description: Ten people, including two con artists and a Hyderabad-based YouTuber who staged a 'fake shooting' to expose the gang, were arrested in Sri Sathya Sai district, Andhra Pradesh. The con artists duped victims by selling fake gold. The YouTuber orchestrated the incident to reveal the scam, using fake pistols and scheduled a meeting with the culprits.
title: Hyderabad YouTuber among 10 arrested for staging 'fake shooting' in Andhra

description: A gym trainer was arrested by Kotwali police for abducting and killing a businessman's wife four months ago. The victim, who trained at the accused's gym, had a heated argument with him before being murdered. Her remains were discovered buried at the Officers Club following the trainer's admission and police investigation.
title: Gym trainer arrested for abducting, killing businessman's wife in UP

description: A viral video of a spat between a Haryana woman police officer and an RSRTC bus conductor has led to RSRTC buses facing penalties in Haryana and Delhi. Approximately 50 buses have been fined for various violations, prompting RSRTC to instruct drivers to adhere strictly to traffic regulations. Officials are investigating the incident and planning discussions with authorities.
title: Spat between bus conductor, Haryana police woman over fare triggers challans

description: New Zealand stunned India with a remarkable 113-run victory in the second Test in Pune, despite missing their star batsman Kane Williamson. Mitchell Santner’s career-best haul of 13-157 and strategic on-field flexibility secured this historic win, ending India's 12-year unbeaten streak at home and impacting their World Test Championship final aspirations.
title: 2nd Test: How Team India's dream run ended with a whimper

description: New Zealand achieved their first-ever Test series win in India by defeating the hosts by 113 runs in Pune. Glenn Phillips highlighted the challenge of competing in India and credited the IPL for his adaptation. Mitchell Santner's exceptional bowling performance was pivotal in the victory. Phillips represents Sunrisers Hyderabad in the IPL.
title: NZ’s IPL advantage: Reason behind India’s defeat

description: Elon Musk allegedly worked illegally in the US during the 1990s while developing his startup, Zip2. He came to Palo Alto in 1995 but did not enroll at Stanford University, potentially violating student work authorization requirements. Musk has not commented on the claims.
title: Elon Musk briefly worked illegally in US in 1990s: Report

description: Former PCB chairman Ramiz Raja faced backlash for taunting Pakistan captain Shan Masood with inappropriate questions after their series win over England. Ramiz's remarks overshadowed Pakistan's comeback victory, leading former cricketers and fans to criticize his lack of professionalism. Mohammad Amir also condemned Ramiz's behavior, urging him to show respect and acknowledge the team's achievements.
title: 'Harkaten padhe-likhon wali karen': Amir blasts Ramiz Raja

description: Indian Army's Romeo Force and the Special Operations Group police uncovered a terrorist hideout in Jammu and Kashmir's Poonch, seizing grenades and Pakistani mines. Security efforts are heightened to find those behind recent attacks in the region. Meanwhile, Counter-Intelligence Kashmir dismantled a recruitment module of Tehreek Labaik Ya Muslim, connected to Lashkar-e-Taiba, across six districts.
title: Army, police bust terrorist hideout in J&K's Poonch

description: With severe air quality days looming, the Centre has urged Punjab and Haryana to utilize all resources to manage stubble burning. Despite a reduction in burning episodes, concerns remain. Financial support and crop residue management strategies are emphasized. Efforts to curb firecrackers during Diwali were also discussed to improve air quality.
title: Bad air: Punjab, Haryana told to be on guard; be strict in farm fire hotspots, says Centre

description: Tesla shares surged 22% after a strong earnings report, boosting CEO Elon Musk's wealth by $26 billion and solidifying his position as the world's richest person with a net worth of $269 billion. Musk's investments in Tesla, SpaceX, X, and xAI continue to drive his financial success.
title: Tesla CEO Elon Musk became $26 billion richer in just one day this week

description: A jury in Delaware awarded Apple $250, concluding that Masimo's older smartwatch designs infringed on Apple's design patents. The jury determined the infringement was intentional, but the verdict's impact is limited to discontinued products, while Masimo emphasizes their current devices are unaffected.
title: Apple gets $250 in smartwatch patent trial: We’re not here for money

description: Former cricketer Anil Kumble expressed disappointment over India's loss to New Zealand in the second Test, attributing it to poor batting. With New Zealand winning their first series in India and leading 2-0, the focus shifts to the final Test in Mumbai. Kumble emphasized the importance of the remaining matches for India's World Test Championship aspirations.
title: 'India made things harder': Cricket legend on WTC Final
Presence of ‘sanghis’ in higher educational institutes up: TN dy CM Udhayanidhi Stalin

description: In Bangarmau, a man named Sharoon, addicted to alcohol, assaulted his wife and fatally threw their two-year-old son, Azaan, to the ground in a drunken rage. The incident occurred on Saturday evening, leading to Sharoon's arrest and the child's body being sent for a post-mortem examination.
title: UP man kills 2-year-old son by throwing him to the ground in fit of rage

description: A sloth bear in Balaghat's Bijora village accidentally ingested a crude bomb meant for wild boars, leading to its death. Officials, including a patrol team and veterinary doctors, investigated and intensified searches to find the individuals responsible for setting the bomb.
title: Wild bear dies after munching crude bomb in MP's Balaghat forest

description: Finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman emphasizes the need for sovereign ratings to properly reflect the economic realities of emerging markets to lower their capital costs. She calls for credit rating agencies to improve their methodologies and highlights the importance of IMF governance reforms amidst global economic challenges.
title: FM Sitharaman pitches for 'fair' sovereign credit ratings, IMF reforms

description: ICICI Bank achieved a record quarterly net profit of Rs 11,746 crore for Q2, a 14.5% rise from last year, with net interest income and deposits showing significant growth. Yes Bank's net profit surged 145.6% to Rs 553 crore, with a significant rise in deposits and advances, despite industry challenges. Both banks reported improved asset quality.
title: ICICI Bank Q2 net jumps 14% to Rs 11,000 crore, Yes Bank's up 145% to Rs 553 crore

description: The Aurangabad bench of Bombay High Court ordered compensations to a man wrongfully arrested under a repealed law, highlighting violations of personal liberty and procedural negligence by police and magistrate. Constable Pandit Tare and Police Inspector Narendra Padalkar were directed to pay Rs2.5 lakh in total.
title: Pay Rs 2.5 lakh to man illegally arrested, court tells cops

description: PM Narendra Modi and his Spanish counterpart Pedro Sanchez will inaugurate the Tata-Airbus C-295 aircraft manufacturing facility in Vadodara. The $2.9 billion project will see 40 of the 56 aircraft made in India, enhancing IAF's tactical airlift capability. The first plane is expected by September 2026, replacing the IAF's aging Avro fleet.
title: PM Modi, Spanish counterpart to inaugurate Tata-Airbus Gujarat plant tomorrow

description: Robert Lewandowski struck twice in three minutes as Barcelona crushed rivals Real Madrid 4-0 on Saturday, inflicting the Spanish champions' first La Liga defeat in over a year. Lamine Yamal and Raphinha scored the other two goals for the Catalans in a night to forget for Carlo Ancelotti's side at the Bernabeu
title: La Liga: Lewandowski scores double as Barcelona shred Real Madrid in Clasico

description: Weekly horoscope provides insight for people on how the planetary placements will affect their zodiac sign. Taurus; With patience and perseverance, you’ll see positive developments at work. Cancer; You may focus on spirituality or seek guidance from elders, which will strengthen your inner resolve. Pisces; With the support of your team, you’ll make important decisions and perform well at work, earning appreciation from your superiors.
title: Weekly horoscope, October 27 to November 2: Read weekly astrological predictions

description: RBI governor Shaktikanta Das anticipates inflation will moderate after October, despite recent highs. Speaking at an IMF-World Bank event, Das emphasized efforts to align inflation with the 4% target and highlighted economic strength. He also warned of cryptocurrency risks and stressed international consensus on regulation.
title: Inflation will begin to cool off after October, says RBI governor

description: New Zealand's cricket team, under Tom Latham's leadership, achieved a landmark 2-0 Test series win against India, breaking their 18-series unbeaten home streak. Latham credited their aggressive strategy and pivotal toss wins as key factors, alongside impressive performances from their bowlers, especially in Bangalore. The series is set to conclude with the third and final Test at Wankhede Stadium in Mumbai, scheduled from November 1 to 5.
title: 'We've fired a shot at Team India': NZ captain

description: ​Amber Rose stirred a social media frenzy after she claimed the Beyonce's speech for Kamala Harris on Friday was copied from the speech that Amber Rose gave for Donald Trump at the Republican National Convention. "She wanna be me so bad. Literally took my whole speech," Amber Rose's comment went viral with people questioning why Beyonce would even try to copy Amber Rose. Social media users also questioned who Amber Rose is and who on earth wants to be Amber Rose.
title: Amber Rose says Beyonce's Harris speech is copied. Social media users ask 'Who are you?'

description: A 53-year-old French tourist, Sylvie Jorji, died under mysterious circumstances in Jaisalmer. She had been ill for two days before being rushed to Jawahir Hospital, where she was declared dead. Sylvie, who had diabetes, was on a three-month tour of India with her husband Lorong.
title: 53-year-old French tourist dies at Rajasthan's Jaisalmer hotel

description: A Mumbai sessions court sentenced Hemant Devrukhakar to life imprisonment for murdering his brother Sainath in 2018. Despite their mother turning hostile in court, the prosecution's evidence proved that Hemant killed Sainath due to his abusive and addictive behavior. Hemant admitted to hitting Sainath with a cement block, causing his death.
title: Brother sentenced to life for murdering elder sibling; mother turns hostile in court

description: Residents in north Bengaluru are set to count potholes on Sandeep Unnikrishnan Road and BEL Road to highlight their poor condition. The roads, part of a major corridor, have numerous potholes causing accidents and delays. Local groups urge BBMP for immediate repairs.
title: Bengaluru residents plan a ‘pothole count’ on Sandeep Unnikrishnan, BEL roads
